emergingmarkets unit that specifically targeted black churches because it figured church leaders had a lot of influence and could convince congregants to take out subprime loans the report goes on to present data from the city of baltimore where more than half the properties subject to foreclosure on a wells fargo loan from  to  now stand vacant and  percent of those are in predominantly black neighborhoods failure to monitor suspected money launderingedit in a march  agreement with federal prosecutors wells fargo acknowledged that between  and  wachovia had failed to monitor and report suspected money laundering by narcotics traffickers including the cash used to buy four planes that shipped a total of  tons of cocaine into mexico overdraft feesedit in august  wells fargo was fined by us district judge william alsup for overdraft practices designed to gouge consumers and profiteer at their expense and for misleading consumers about how the bank processed transactions and assessed overdraft fees settlement and fines regarding mortgage servicing practicesedit on february   it was announced that the five largest mortgage servicers allygmac bank of america citi jpmorgan chase and wells fargo agreed to a settlement with the federal government and  states the settlement known as the national mortgage settlement nms required the servicers to provide about  billion in relief to distressed homeowners and in direct payments to the states and federal government this settlement amount makes the nms the second largest civil settlement in us history only trailing the tobacco master settlement agreement the five banks were also required to comply with  new mortgage servicing standards oklahoma held out and agreed to settle with the banks separately on april   a federal judge ordered wells fargo to pay  million in punitive damages over a single loan one of the largest fines for a bank ever for mortgaging service misconduct elizabeth magner a federal bankruptcy judge in the eastern district of louisiana cited the banks behavior as highly reprehensible stating that wells fargo has taken advantage of borrowers who rely on the banks accurate calculations she went on to add perhaps more disturbing is wells fargos refusal to voluntarily correct its errors it prefers to rely on the ignorance of borrowers or their inability to fund a challenge to its demands rather than voluntarily relinquish gains obtained through improper accounting methods alleged racial discrimination during foreclosuresedit in  the department of housing and urban development hud launched an investigation of wells fargo for racial discrimination practices the second federal probe in  of alleged violations of misconduct with regard to race the other began in  by the national fair housing alliance has found overwhelming and troubling evidence that six of the nations major banks handle foreclosures in neighborhoods populated primarily by minorities differently than in white communities on july   wells fargo entered a settlement agreement with the us department of justice for allegedly discriminating against africanamerican and hispanic borrowers from  to  wells fargo agreed to pay  million to subprime borrowers and  million in direct down payment assistance in certain areas for a total of  million wells fargo spokespersons denied all claims and are settling only to avoid contested litigation sec fine due to inadequate risk disclosuresedit on august   wells fargo agreed to pay around  million to settle sec charges that in  it sold risky mortgagebacked securities without fully realizing their dangers lawsuit by fha over loan underwritingedit on october   the us federal government sued the bank under the false claims act at the federal court in manhattan new york the suit alleges that wells fargo defrauded the federal housing administration fha over the past ten years underwriting over  fha backed loans when over half did not qualify for the program this suit is the third allegation levied against wells fargo in  in october  wells fargo was sued by us federal attorney preet bharara over questionable mortgage deals lawsuit due to premium inflation on forced place insuranceedit in april  wells fargo settled a suit with  florida homeowners alongside insurer qbe in which wells fargo was accused of inflating premiums on forcedplace insurance lawsuit regarding excessive overdraft feesedit in may  wells fargo paid  million to settle classaction litigation accusing the bank of imposing excessive overdraft fees on checkingaccount customers also in may the new york attorneygeneral eric schneiderman announced a lawsuit against wells fargo over alleged violations of the national mortgage settlement a  billion deal struck between  state attorneys and the fivelargest mortgage servicers in the us schneidermann claimed wells fargo had violated rules over giving fair and timely serving  violation of new york credit card lawsedit in february  wells fargo agreed to pay  million for violations where an affiliate took interest in the homes of borrowers in exchange for opening credit card accounts for the homeowners this is illegal according to new york credit card laws there was a  million penalty with the other  million going towards restitution to customers executive compensationedit with ceo john stumpf being paid  times more than the median employee wells fargo ranks number  among the sp  companies for ceo–employee pay inequality in october  a wells fargo employee earning  per hour emailed the ceo – copying  other employees – asking that all employees be given a  per year raise taken from a portion of annual corporate profits to address wage stagnation and income inequality after being contacted by the media wells fargo responded that all employees receive market competitive pay and benefits significantly above federal minimums tax avoidance and lobbyingedit in december  the nonpartisan organization public campaign criticized wells fargo for spending  million on