 wellsfargoworkscom and entering a website that wells fargo does not control wells fargo has provided this link for your convenience but does not endorse and is not responsible for the content links privacy policy or security policy of this website cancel continue planning business plan center writing a business plan starting a business business lifecycle leadership retirement and transition plans marketing marketing center market research marketing tactics managing products and services sales methods measuring roi management financials and cash flow employee management legal and regulations insurance taxes and accounting credit business credit center credit history financing and working capital credit options applications credit management insights small business index millennial small business owner study diverse segments lending study our experts about us contact us visit wellsfargocom español how to conduct sales forecasting for a new product or service skip to main content visit wellsfargocom español contact us search submit click to open menu search submit share business plan center how to conduct sales forecasting for a new product or service sales forecasts must be a part of your new product launch process how can i project sales for new products and services sales projections impact your businesss cash flow pricing inventory and more and they should guide your daily operations but what if youre launching a brandnew product or service or what if youre a brandnew business owner how do you forecast sales creating sales forecasts can be challenging — for firsttime entrepreneurs and for existing owners with new offerings but it doesnt have to be here are two methods you can use to produce useful sales projections method  topdown sales forecasting this method is based on determining the total market that exists for your industry and area then estimating your share of that market say you own a restaurant and discover that consumers spend  million annually on dining out in your state with that bigpicture information you might estimate that you can corner  of the market and make  in annual sales to create a topdown sales forecast research total sales data for your industry estimate how much of the market your business will land and base your forecasts on that figure remember to be realistic though because this method starts with highlevel data it can be easy to overestimate your potential market share  best way to do a market analysis inc  httpwwwinccomjeffhadenbottomuportopdownmarketanalysiswhichshouldyouusehtml what is topdown forecasting demand media  httpsmallbusinesschroncomtopdownforecastinghtml topdown sales forecasting tips before you start a topdown sales forecast find useful sales data in addition to general industry statistics you can look for information on businesses that offer the same products or services you do here are some research tips look online for press releases pricing data and financial reports your competitors may publish salesrelated statistics especially if they want to showcase recent success read trade publications and industry newsletters which report on notable competitors as well as industrywide sales trends visit your competitors brickandmortar and online stores their inventory pricing and marketing materials can reveal their sales strategies if you cant find direct competitors research businesses that offer similar products or services even if you have unique offerings theres probably an existing product or service to use as a baseline when fax machines were invented for instance analysts projected their sales using data from typewriters and copiers  creating a sales forecast entrepreneur  httpwwwentrepreneurcomarticle method  bottomup sales forecasting this method is based on estimating your potential sales to predict a total sales figure there may be a demand for  units of your product or service but that information wont help you create a sales forecast if you can only produce  units to create a bottomup sales forecast estimate how many products or services you can make and sell given your facilities sales team and other factors then multiply the number of potential sales by your average sale price to forecast your total sales volume  what is topdown forecasting demand media  httpsmallbusinesschroncomtopdownforecastinghtml how to do a market analysis for a business plan the business plan shop  httpswwwthebusinessplanshopcomblogenentrymarketanalysisforbusinessplan best way to do a market analysis inc  httpwwwinccomjeffhadenbottomuportopdownmarketanalysiswhichshouldyouusehtml bottomup sales forecasting tips one way to forecast sales from the bottom up is to break your product or service down into units lawyers for instance sell their services by the hour and taxi companies sell by the ride project your sales by breaking down your product or service into similar units and then estimating how many units you can realistically sell in a given time period if you run a restaurant break it down into meals how many customers can you serve at once how many tables and chairs do you have how much will the average customer spend on a meal analyze your menu to find a benchmark price starting with simple units can help you begin your projections itll involve some educated guessing but it will make firsttime forecasting easier  how to forecast sales for a new product or service allbusiness  httpwwwallbusinesscombusinessplanningstructuresbusinessplanshtml be realistic with new product sales forecasting as you prepare to launch a new product or service think about how you can create useful and realistic sales projections try using the topdown and bottomup methods for more information and consider other indicators of future sales such as traffic to your website and expectations of seasonal demand during the holidays your early forecasts should be conservative but careful research can help you gauge how new offerings will perform you might also plan for an initial shortterm bump in sales from curious firsttime customers by ensuring that you have sufficient inventory to meet the demand  forecasting sales for your startup business page bizfilings  httpwwwbizfilingscomtoolkitsbgstartupfinancingforecastingsalesforyourstartupaspx published april   tags sales forecasting product development business plan share business creditcenter get started go to the business credit center wells fargogallup small business index see how business owners rate their current and future financial situations learn more you may also like business plan center tips for creating accurate cash flow forecasts go to article business plan center sales forecasting basics a checklist go to article marketing center three strategies to drive business growth go to article talk with a banker make an appointment or call us now at  find an atm or awells fargo location enter zip or city and state connect with wells fargo works go to the linkedin page for wells fargo works go to the facebook page for wells fargo works go to the twitter page for wells fargo works go to the youtube page for wells fargo works about wells fargo vision and values corporate social responsibility working at wells fargo investor relations newsroom atmlocations customer service report fraud sitemap diversity  accessibility privacy cookies and security  legal atmlocations customer service report fraud sitemap diversity  accessibility privacy cookies and security  legal information and views provided through the wells fargo works for small business website are general in nature for your consideration and are not legal tax or investment advice wells fargo makes no warranties as to accuracy or completeness of information including but not limited to information provided by third parties does not endorse any nonwells fargo companies products or services described here and takes no liability for your use of this information information and suggestions regarding business risk management and safeguards do not