men’s leadership initiative membership member benefits membership application events news uli in action advisory services building healthy places initiative community building distinction awards marketplace conference public sector leaders university outreach urban innovation toolkit sponsorship annual sponsor benefits event sponsorship blog contact uli houston news wells fargo foundation and uli building better professionals posted on december   by dianebarber sharesharetweetsharepin itemail houston – august    – the houston district council of the urban land institute uli announced that wells fargo foundation has renewed its underwriting support as benefactor of the uli houston young leader mentorship program “uli is grateful to wells fargo foundation the founding underwriter of the uli houston young leader mentorship program and the phase  graduate student mentorship program” said ann taylor executive director of the urban land institute houston district council “wells fargo foundation’s support enables uli to offer this invaluable program at no cost to the participants” nipul v patel senior vice president regional manager commercial real estate for wells fargo  company said the ability to connect young professionals with role models who are accomplished real estate professionals and who also embrace the uli code of ethics appealed to the wells fargo foundation “young professionals today are stepping up to take on responsibilities that will shape the future of the industry and of our cities” patel said “transferring the wisdom of hardearned experience from veteran leaders instills the importance of doing the right thing the ripple effect of this transfer of knowledge is making a positive contribution to communities” uli houston pioneered the young leaders program in  it was the first young leader program within uli and now has spread across the country and globally to  countries in europe and six in asiapacific offered at no additional cost to uli members less than  years old the young leaders program now has more than  members in  the houston district council created the uli young leader mentorship program underwritten by wells fargo to provide an opportunity for uli young leaders and veteran uli members to create lasting professional relationships by sharing knowledge and experiences in an intimate smallgroup setting after graduating from the yearlong program with their mentors uli young leaders then “pay it forward” by becoming mentors to graduate real estate students at area universities “this has been one of the most rewarding and enjoyable experiences of my career to get to know these incredibly talented and professional young business men and women “said w douglas goff chief operating officer of the johnson development corp “i dare say that i have gained as much or more from the program as the ‘mentees’” one of the unique strengths of the uli houston young leader mentorship program is that it was created by young leaders to address a knowledge gap the young leaders had identified founding chairs of the uli houston young leader mentorship program were anna autin and matthew behrmann both employees of hines a global real estate firm founded by uli trustee gerald d hines “the uli young leader mentorship program is a continuation on the local level of the commitment of leading organizations to improve the quality of tomorrow’s leaders” behrmann said  “mentors are selected based on their professional accomplishments and outstanding reputations and young leaders also are selected for their ability to contribute to the overall quality of the program as well” current uli young leader mentors  alan arnold rice management company alan patton morgan group mike mair skanska ted nelson newland communities susan hill hff learn more on our website wwwhoustonuliorg about the urban land institute the urban land institute wwwuliorg is a global nonprofit education and research institute supported by its members its mission is to provide leadership in the responsible use of land and in creating and sustaining thriving communities worldwide established in  the institute has more than  members representing all aspects of land use the houston district council is uli at the local level facilitating the exchange of ideas and the transmission of uli best practices uli houston has more than  members who come together at educational programs and other events to share experiences and learn from each other about wells fargo wells fargo  company nyse wfc is a nationwide diversified communitybased financial services company with  trillion in assets founded in  and headquartered in san francisco wells fargo provides banking insurance investments mortgage and consumer and commercial finance through more than  locations  atms and the internet wellsfargocom and has offices in  countries to support customers who conduct business in the global economy with more than  team members wells fargo serves one in three households in the united states wells fargo  company was ranked no  on fortune’s  rankings of america’s largest corporations wells fargo’s vision is to satisfy all our customers’ financial needs and help them succeed financially wells fargo perspectives and stories are also available at blogswellsfargocom and at wellsfargocomstories – see more at httphoustonuliorgnewsdetailwellsfargofoundationandulibuildingbetterprofessionalssthashayexnndpuf sharesharetweetsharepin itemail this entry was posted in news bookmark the permalink leave a reply cancel reply your email address will not be published required fields are marked comment name  email  website   categories blog news video profile archives june  may  april  march  january  december  november  october  september  august  july  april  march  february  january  december  november  october  september  august  july  june  may  april  march  february  january  december  july  june  april  february  january  december  november  october  september  august  june  m